. It cost a 'not so cheap' reagent to cast the thing and most times it is resisted.<br>
<br>
If anything, this should be equal to the Rogues Assasinate, no? Hell, give it a level limit and a percentage like crit hits. Take the friggin spell out of the game and make it for all DDs to have a chance. I do not care if it is 2%. It would still be more useful then it is now.<br>
<br>
I did notice that when doing Aary and fighting those lil drakelings before him, you can use it there. But you have to have Encs Tash the things and then you STILL will get resisted. They are level 46 below by the way. Otherwise our Enc's could not Dire Charm them and use them against Aary =P<br>
<br>
Anyway, this is just an opinion from an old wizard.<br>
<br>
 <p><b><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4623>Master Kalvorie Ra`Baenre</a><BR> Dark Elf Sorcerer<BR><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdeadlyvirtues>Deadly Virtues</a></b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/8/02 2:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well...</span><hr size=1> Making it like another class is inheritly undesirable.  =)<br>
<br>
If they made it increase in level cap after L 60, it would help its usefulness.  Imagine if at L 65 you could disintegrate L 50 mobs?<br>
<br>
... ok, still less than awe inspiring.  =)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usamadhibots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samadhi BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>TrollGuard 2000<BR><a href=mailto:samadhi@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><u>Contact Samadhi</u></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 3663<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/8/02 2:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disintegrate = Useless... This should be changed</span><hr size=1> It's great for mid-level dungeons such as the Hole for getting rid of Green adds very, very fast. It's also good for getting rid of High-level MOB's pets. It's not entirely useless, it has its purposes.<br>
<br>
However, they need to remove the reagent for the spell. With the recast delay and mana cost, and the fact that it can be resisted, there's no reason it should have a reagent. If they took it away, it'd be a great situational spell. <p><a href="http://store4.yimg.com/I/demotivators_1697_691386"><P align=center>
