<br>
Just to be kind, It should only cost 5 mana to cast, and take about .5 seconds though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 6167<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/19/02 11:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: useless...?</span><hr size=1> No, all that's needed is a line of Knock spells that give roughly the same ability of a rogue (slightly lower) of that level (at level 20, it has an effective lockpick of 90, for example).  The casting time and mana cost are meaningless, you won't be picking locks in an emergency very often.  With a mana cost it will always be preferable to have a rogue, since doors close after a while and stay locked: how often does everyone make it through on the first try?<br>
<br>
